    "title": "Immediate Requirement Store Manager at Marks & Spencer India International Enterprises",
    "description": "Join the Marks & Spencer India International Enterprises family as a Store Manager in Vijayawada. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Marks & Spencer India International Enterprises:\nMarks & Spencer India International Enterprises is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Handle customer queries, complaints, and escalations effectively\n• Monitor inventory levels and coordinate replenishment activities\n• Coordinate with the supply chain team for timely stock delivery\n• Prepare daily sales reports and share insights with management\n• Conduct regular stock audits and prevent pilferage\n• Manage shrinkage and reduce stock discrepancies\n• Ensure compliance with company policies and retail regulations\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in KPI Management\n• Proficiency in Planogram\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain\n• Proficiency in Visual Merchandising\n• Proficiency in E-commerce Integration\n• Proficiency in Inventory Management\n• Proficiency in Loss Prevention\n• Proficiency in Sales Techniques\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Flexible working hours\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Marks & Spencer India International Enterprises!",
